message.content: cs.HC, cs.BIO, cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.NEURON - The paper focuses on developing a clustering algorithm for surface electromyography (sEMG) data collected from the clinical environment to classify cervical spondylosis (CS) dysfunction. This involves the use of cervical structure, cervical vertebra function, and sEMG data, which are related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC), bioinformatics (cs.BIO), machine learning (cs.LG), computer engineering (cs.CE), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NEURON).
